caption: I attended Dr. Eladio Dieguez's office for an appointment with my mom, who is his patient. At the end of the appointment, I had to congratulate Dr. Dieguez for his great care. Very attentive and detailed. Thank you Doctor for the great work you are doing.

I don't like to go to doctors, I only go when I have no other choice. When I 1st met Dr. Dieguez  I found him to be very professional and sometimes that can come across as cold. But he is far from cold. He sent me for the test I needed to help us get the big picture of my health. After the test all we could do is wait. These test and the results were very important and possibly life changing. Due to personal reasons I had to get the results over the phone. When he called and spoke with me, he was so kind, he gave me the results waited for me to process them and then he answered all my questions and waited on phone till I was ready to hang up. But before I did he assured me I was not alone, and that he'd be praying for me. I will never forget the results of the test or the effect it has had on my life, But I will remember the kindness and compassion in his voice more. Though I was happy with my previous Dr, I changed my healthcare plan so I had to switch doctors. I selected Dr. Suzanne Johnson on Fruitville Rd. My first visit with Dr. Johnson was in June. I was impressed with m Dr. Johnson right off as she spent over an hour with me and went over all previous records that had been forward but also requested additional information, ie. pathology reports, not relying on basic statements on my records. This week, I had an episode of vertigo and called Dr. Johnson’s office for a referral to an ENT Doctor to have a procedure to resolve the vertigo. Her office advised that Dr. Johnson could do the procedure and scheduled a visit just 2 days later. I went for the procedure today and was totally blown away. Dr. Johnson not only performed the procedure but showed me exercises I could do every day to help prevent having this problem reoccur. I’ve been to ENT Dr’s twice before and was never shown these exercises. Additionally, Dr. Johnson gave me a printout showing these exercises to help me know just how to do them. I was initially skeptical about changing doctors but believe this change will truly be beneficial for me. Additionally, I had no co-pay for a specialist. Dr. Johnson is, in my opinion, excellent and is dedicated to her patients. I’m thrilled!

Again, felt very weird.  I was asked again if I had been vaccinated.  (I had previously given my Covid vaccine cards to staff to copy for my file).    She complained her internet was spotty.  On my previous visit, she left the exam room for 7” to ask the tavern next door to turn down their music.  Every single time I have seen her, she looks up medical information while sitting next to me and reads it to me.  I can do this myself at home.  She looks more at her laptop than at me which I find distracting.  She seemed distracted and not happy.  The entire visit was negative.  She reduced an Rx without offering me any kind of safety net or suggestions/modifications to improve my symptoms.  She also said she would no longer prescribe another Rx she had previously given me.  The third Rx I requested to reduce pain (not anything addictive, nor an opiod), she refused.  I called a few days later and asked to see two specialists.  One of them, without hesitation, prescribed the medicine she refused.  He realized the necessity of the Rx.  She entered an incorrect diagnosis for a referral to a specialist and her office seemed unwilling to correct the mistake.  She finished by saying that I needed to come in every month to replenish an Rx vs. every 3 months I had been seeing her.  Feels like she’s padding her wallet.  Someone else might have a better experience, but I felt such relief when I requested my medical records be sent to a compassionate and caring physician that wants to work with me as a partner in my health vs. against me.
